org.orgName: United States District Court for the District of Washington

div1.ab: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Lee Fong for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
div1.p: On this 2nd day of September, 1902, upon consideration of the petition for a Writ of Habeas Corpus herein,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that JOHN SULLIVAN, Chief of Police of the City of Seattle, appear in this court at the court room in the City of Seattle, appear in this court at the court room in the City of Seattle, at 10 o'clock A.M., on Friday, September 5th, 1902, then and there to show cause if he can why a Writ of Habeas Corpus should not be issued as prayed for in said petition.
div1.ab: FILED IN THE U.S. District Court, DIST. OF WASHINGTON.
Dist. of Washington Office of U.S. Marshal
div1.p: I hereby certify that I received this forgoing writ on the 2d day of Sept. 1902, and that on said 2d day of Sept. 1902. I personally served the same on John Sullivan, Chief of Police at his office in the City of Seattle, by delivering to and handing with him a true and correct copy thereof-
div1.ab: C.B. Hopkins U. S. marshal By H. W. Tyler, Deputy.
Dated Seattle Wash This 3rd day of Sept 1902-
IN THE District COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON
In the Matter of the Application of Lee Fong for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
